21/03/2004
BRATISLAVA, Slovakia -- Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader met with EU Enlargement Commissioner Gunter Verheugen and NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer on the sidelines of the conference in Bratislava on Friday (19 March) and asked for more reassurance about Croatia's possible membership in the two organisations.
Sanader specified that Croatia would like to receive stronger reassurance about its NATO membership at the Istanbul summit in June.
Verheugen will pay a two-day visit to Croatia in late May to discuss the country's EU membership prospects.
(HINA, Croatian Radio - 19/03/04)
